      • getModels

        @NotNull
public final List<SModel> getModels()
        Specified by:
        getModels in interface ModelRoot
        Returns:
        a sequence of the models under this model root. Implementors must impose some order on the returned result, such that two consequent invocations of this method return equal results. Note that owning module also returns all the models (module is believed to be a model container) SModule.getModels(), however it might contain the models which are not attached to the model roots as well (!)

      • update

        public void update()
        IMPORTANT API METHOD Tricky logic which is forced onto all of subclasses. This method represents a caching mechanism which does not reload the models which are already loaded but looks only at the difference between what we had and what we get now Strangely enough this logic is not in API (not added to the API #loadModels implementation) so the client of this class (and its subclasses) has to cast his ModelRoot to ModelRootBase every time he wants to reload the models from their data sources.
